  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Kansas has received $2.5B in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. There were 17,194 awards with an average award size of $143K, and obligations fell 31.3% year over year. The current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). The Department of Veterans Affairs accounted for $1.5B of obligations, and the Department of Transportation and Department of Defense contributed $455M and $408M respectively. On the vendor side, ORACLE HEALTH GOVERNMENT SERVICES, INC. received $1.3B and INDRA AIR TRAFFIC, INC. received $374M. At the industry level, Computer Systems Design Services accounted for $1.3B and Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing accounted for $373M. Historical fiscal-year obligations show variation: FY21 was $2.9B, FY22 was $4.2B, FY23 was $3B, FY24 was $3.3B, FY25 was $3.6B, and FY26 is $2.5B to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have federal contract obligations changed year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 31.3% year over year in FY2026 to date. Annual obligations varied over the last six fiscal years: FY21 was $2.9B, FY22 was $4.2B, FY23 was $3B, FY24 was $3.3B, FY25 was $3.6B, and FY26 is $2.5B to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate FY2026 federal contracting in Kansas?",
        "body": "The Department of Veterans Affairs is the largest buying agency with $1.5B in obligations, followed by the Department of Transportation with $455M and the Department of Defense with $408M. ORACLE HEALTH GOVERNMENT SERVICES, INC. is the top vendor with $1.3B, followed by INDRA AIR TRAFFIC, INC. with $374M and TEXTRON AVIATION INC with $82.2M."
      }
    ]
  },
